-- Ireland Homebuyers Used Cash for 50% of 1H Purchases, Post Says
-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 2012-10-07T11:35:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-07/ireland-homebuyers-used-cash-for-50-of-1h-purchases-post-says.html
Cash buyers accounted for half of all
residential property sales in first 6 months of year, Sunday
Business Post says.
* EU1.94b of property sold in 1H, paper says
* EU1.66b spent in 1H of previous year
* NOTE: Irish  home prices  have fallen by about 50% since 2007  To contact the reporter on this story:
